description: Try our easy to follow Rosemary & Olive Wreath recipe. Absolutely delicious with the best ingredients from Woolworths.
keywords: Pastries,Pescatarian,Halal,Christmas,Soy free,Vegetarian,Tree nut free,Low sugar,Sesame free,Peanut free
name: Rosemary & Olive Wreath Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 0.25 cup black olives, pitted, finely chopped

recipeInstructions.text: Stir oil and garlic in a bowl and season well. In a separate bowl, mix parmesan, olives and chopped rosemary to combine.

Lay 1 pastry sheet on a clean surface, covering remaining sheets with a damp cloth to prevent drying. Brush with garlic oil, then top with a second sheet and brush with garlic oil. Repeat until you have a stack of 4 sheets. Sprinkle with 2 tbs parmesan mixture, then repeat oiling and layering until you’ve used half the filo sheets. Starting from one long edge, roll into a log. Brush top with garlic oil and set aside. Repeat to make a second log.
Preheat oven to 200°C. Line a large baking tray with baking paper.

Halve each log down the centre lengthways. With cut sides facing up, braid the 2 halves together and transfer to tray. Shape into a semicircle. Repeat with remaining halves. Join semi-circles by overlapping ends to form a wreath.
Brush with any remaining garlic oil and sprinkle with extra parmesan.
Bake for 2530 minutes or until golden and crisp. Serve warm garnished with extra rosemary.
